        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 1:06PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 106 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bend, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Saba, Cherokee, Colorado Bend State Park, Bend, Chappel,
Harkeyville, and Us-190 Near The San Saba-Lampasas County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
